<h2>
    Fishing Tactics for Medford’s Lakes and Rivers
</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Still Fishing</strong>: PowerBait, worms, and salmon eggs for stocked trout.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Trolling</strong>: Flashers and spoons for deeper lakes like Lost Creek and Applegate.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Drift Fishing</strong>: Roe and yarn for steelhead in the Rogue.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Bass Techniques</strong>: Soft plastics, spinnerbaits, and jigs in Emigrant and Agate Lakes.
    </li>
</ul>
<h2>
    Fly Fishing Opportunities Near Medford
</h2>
<p>
    Fly anglers love Southern Oregon for:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Rogue River</strong>: Dry-dropper setups and swing flies for steelhead.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Applegate River</strong>: Great for indicator nymphing and small streamers.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Bear Creek &amp; Small Tributaries</strong>: Use Elk Hair Caddis, Adams, and Prince Nymphs.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    A 5–6 wt rod is perfect for trout; use 7–8 wt gear for steelhead.
</p>
